Note:
Annotation Constants - Canonical Type IDs for All 22 Block Annotation Types

Pure constants file with zero imports. Defines the complete set of block annotation
type IDs, category classifications, target validity flags, parse status flags, and
field type constants used throughout the annotation subsystem.

Block annotation IDs use the 9000-range to avoid collision with:
- AI annotation types (1-8 in annotation_parser.runa)
- Type annotation types (1-23 in type_annotations.runa)
- AST node types (1000-8999 in ast.runa)

IDs are grouped by category with gaps between groups to allow future expansion
within each category without renumbering.

Reference: docs/user/language-specification/runa_annotation_system.md
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Block Annotation Type IDs (9000-9099 range)
Note: ============================================================================

Note: --- Category 1: Reasoning and Intent ---
Note: Documents the logical reasoning process and decision rationale
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_REASONING as Integer is 9001
Note: Provides detailed implementation notes, steps, invariants, and guidance
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_IMPLEMENTATION as Integer is 9002

Note: --- Category 2: Uncertainty and Confidence ---
Note: Declares alternatives with confidence levels for AI selection
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_UNCERTAINTY as Integer is 9010

Note: --- Category 3: Knowledge and Context ---
Note: Links implementation to external knowledge sources (DOIs, papers, specs)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_KNOWLEDGE_REFERENCE as Integer is 9020
Note: Provides situational context (deployment environment, constraints, platform)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_CONTEXT as Integer is 9021

Note: --- Category 4: Task and Specification ---
Note: Formal task specification with objectives, inputs, outputs, acceptance criteria
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_TASK as Integer is 9030
Note: Detailed functional and non-functional requirements
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_REQUIREMENTS as Integer is 9031

Note: --- Category 5: Verification and Quality ---
Note: Embedded verification conditions (Assert invariants and postconditions)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_VERIFY as Integer is 9040
Note: Comprehensive test specifications (unit, integration, performance)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_TEST_CASES as Integer is 9041

Note: --- Category 6: Resource and Security ---
Note: Computational and memory limitations (budget, timeout, memory cap)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_RESOURCE_CONSTRAINTS as Integer is 9050
Note: Security capabilities and restrictions (allowed/forbidden actions, sandbox)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_SECURITY_SCOPE as Integer is 9051

Note: --- Category 7: Execution and Performance ---
Note: Execution mode preferences (batch/streaming/real-time, concurrency, scheduling)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_EXECUTION_MODEL as Integer is 9060
Note: Optimization guidance (cache strategy, vectorization, parallel thresholds)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_PERFORMANCE_HINTS as Integer is 9061

Note: --- Category 8: Communication ---
Note: Real-time progress reporting (completion %, milestones, blockers)
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_PROGRESS as Integer is 9070
Note: Review feedback and iteration notes
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_FEEDBACK as Integer is 9071
Note: Questions requiring human or AI clarification
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_REQUEST_CLARIFICATION as Integer is 9072
Note: Explicit requests to AI agents
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_REQUEST as Integer is 9073
Note: Resolved clarifications preserved for reference
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_CLARIFICATION as Integer is 9074

Note: --- Category 9: Translation ---
Note: Target-language-specific adaptation notes for cross-language translation
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_TRANSLATION_NOTE as Integer is 9080

Note: --- Category 10: Error Handling ---
Note: Error handling strategies, recovery policies, retry logic
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_ERROR_HANDLING as Integer is 9090

Note: --- Category 11: Collaboration and Iteration ---
Note: Multi-agent coordination directives for AI collaboration
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_COLLABORATION as Integer is 9095
Note: Iterative refinement tracking across development cycles
Constant BLOCK_ANNOTATION_ITERATION as Integer is 9096

