Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Target Validity Flags (bitmask, combinable via bitwise OR)
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Each annotation type declares which code elements it may be attached to.
Note: These are bitmask flags that can be combined (e.g., PROCESS + TYPE = 3).

Constant ANNOTATION_TARGET_PROCESS as Integer is 1     Note: Bit 0 - Function/Process definitions
Constant ANNOTATION_TARGET_TYPE as Integer is 2        Note: Bit 1 - Type/Struct definitions
Constant ANNOTATION_TARGET_MODULE as Integer is 4      Note: Bit 2 - Module-level (import scope)
Constant ANNOTATION_TARGET_FILE as Integer is 8        Note: Bit 3 - File-level (top of file)
Constant ANNOTATION_TARGET_BLOCK as Integer is 16      Note: Bit 4 - Any code block
Constant ANNOTATION_TARGET_ALL as Integer is 31        Note: All bits set (valid everywhere)

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parse Status Flags
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Indicates whether the bootstrap compiler currently parses this annotation
Note: type as a structured block or merely recognizes it in the lexer.

Constant ANNOTATION_STATUS_PARSED as Integer is 1      Note: Currently parsed by bootstrap (14 types)
Constant ANNOTATION_STATUS_RESERVED as Integer is 2    Note: Recognized by lexer but not routed (8 types)

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Field Value Type Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Each annotation field has an expected value type. These constants classify
Note: what kind of data a field holds for validation purposes.

Constant FIELD_TYPE_STRING as Integer is 1             Note: Single string value
Constant FIELD_TYPE_INTEGER as Integer is 2            Note: Integer value
Constant FIELD_TYPE_FLOAT as Integer is 3              Note: Floating-point value
Constant FIELD_TYPE_LIST as Integer is 4               Note: List of values (strings, ints, etc.)
Constant FIELD_TYPE_DICTIONARY as Integer is 5         Note: Key-value pairs
Constant FIELD_TYPE_BOOLEAN as Integer is 6            Note: true/false
Constant FIELD_TYPE_FREEFORM as Integer is 7           Note: Arbitrary text content (no structured fields)

Constant FIELD_TYPE_COUNT as Integer is 7
